      "author": "JayJiangCT",
      "description": "## Internal beta\n\n- Keeps maintenance and system activity receipts out of Today active knowledge threads while still counting recent agent work.\n- Adds source.surface to distinguish knowledge activity from system, setup, audit, and maintenance logs.\n- Appends a compact Activity Ledger reminder to Knowlery agent handoff prompts without exposing JSONL schema.\n- Accepts both strict JSONL and pretty-printed activity receipt objects.\n- Tightens first-cook prompts so maintenance findings are summarized in chat by default.\n- Strengthens Obsidian CLI and Activity Ledger guidance for Claude Code.\n- Polishes Today suggested-step buttons into compact action rows.\n\n## Validation\n\n- npm test\n- npm run build\n\n## Beta notes\n\nThis prerelease is intended for Jay WorkSpace validation of first-cook, Claudian handoff, Activity Ledger receipts, and Today state boundaries. Reload Obsidian/Knowlery after updating through BRAT or release assets.",
